The '''Core World Critics Association''' was an association of [[Holodrama/Legends|holodrama]] critics that was composed of the some of the most influential media critics of the [[Core Worlds/Legends|Core Worlds]]. They gathered annually to discuss the year's holofilms. During their gathering in <ref name="Hnn" /> [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]],<ref name="22 BBY">The [[Great ReSynchronization|date]] 13:3:14 corresponds to [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]] per the reasoning [[Template:YearMathGRS|here]].</ref> the president was [[Jaysa Namoor]]. That same year, they criticized the writing quality standards of the films of the upcoming summer season.<ref name="Hnn">{{HoloNetNewsWeb|48|life/13321_1.html|Holo Critics Preemptively Bemoan Summer Season}}</ref> The films they preemptively panned included ''[[Another Idiot's Array 2]]'', ''[[Cataclysm Prism 4]]'', ''[[Crimson Empire III]]'', ''[[Whelping Day]]'', ''[[Split Infinitive]]'', ''[[Lightspeed Lightweight]]'', ''[[Tenta-kill 5]]'', and ''[[A Google of Gornts]]''.<ref name="Hnn" />

